sharon saez understanding language stanford university school of education understanding language home project description steering committee staff faqs sharon saez home sharon saez sharon saez is the program director for english language learners ell and inclusion for the standards assessments and accountability strategic initiative at the council of chief state school officers she manages both the english language development assessment and english language learners collaborative in these past three years serves as a core member of the council's leadership team contribute knowledge and expertise in the area of standards based accountability in k 12 education policy and oversee implementation of projects to enhance current education practices and advises the council and state educational agencies on policy matters relating to the inclusion of english language learners low performing and disenfranchised populations and students with special needs in educational assessment programs website contact info martha castellon executive director 650 248 1177 mcastel stanford edu kenji hakuta principal investigator and co chair of the steering committee 650 723 5620 hakuta stanford edu mail martha castellon or kenji hakuta school of education stanford university 485 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 3096 social media facebook twitter subscribe to our email list stanford university school of education 485 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 3096 copyright 2011 stanford university all rights reserved
